Astra, Aneka Tambang, United Tractors: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-09-16T01:32:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/astra-aneka-tambang-united-tractors-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  fell 0.7 percent to 3,774.33.  Nickel producers: Nickel for three-month delivery gained 2
percent to $21,800 a metric ton in  London  yesterday, rising for
a second day. PT International Nickel Indonesia (INCO IJ), the
nation’s biggest producer of the metal, declined 3.4 percent to
3,600 rupiah and PT Aneka Tambang (ANTM IJ), the second largest,
fell 2.2 percent to 1,780 rupiah.  PT Astra International (ASII IJ): Indonesia’s domestic
vehicle sales in August dropped 18 percent from a month earlier
to 73,279 units,  Bisnis Indonesia  reported, citing data from the
nation’s automotive industries association. Astra, Indonesia’s
biggest automotive retailer, fell 2.2 percent to 65,300 rupiah.  PT Nusantara Infrastructure (META IJ): The construction
company will acquire a water company at an estimated value of
500 billion rupiah ($57 million) next month or in November,
Investor Daily  Indonesia  reported, citing Managing Director
Bernardus Djonoputro. Nusantara rose 2.4 percent to 210 rupiah.  PT United Tractors (UNTR IJ): Indonesia’s biggest heavy
equipment seller expects 2012 coal production to rise 22 percent
from this year to 5.5 million tons, Kontan reported, citing
Corporate Secretary Sara Loebis. United Tractors slipped 0.9
percent to 22,900 rupiah.  PT XL Axiata (EXCL IJ): The mobile-phone operator is
considering selling bonds and seeking bank loans to raise 10
trillion rupiah over the next three years to expand its business
and repay debt, Investor Daily Indonesia reported, citing
President Director Hasnul Suhaimi. The stock gained 3 percent to
5,150 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  